Actual spending for 2019-20 is $191.7 million (26%) higher than expenditures in 2018-19. The increase is mainly due to:  
• An increase in payments for the Disaster Financial Assistance Arrangements program ($90.1 million);  
• A one-time statutory grant to the Shock Trauma Air Rescue Service ($65 million);  
• A one-time endowment to support Avalanche Canada ($25 million);  
• An increase in payments for the Take Action Against Gun and Gang Violence initiative ($19.8 million); and  
• An increase in payments to PTs for the National Disaster Mitigation Program ($13 million).  

Offset by:  
• Contribution payments to provinces and territories in support of Canada’s 2018 G7 Presidency in Charlevoix, Quebec, which took place in June 2018 ($61.2 million).  

In 2019–20, the Main Estimates and Planned Spending increased by $231.6 million (31%) to a Total Authorities Available for Use of $974.6 million. The increase is mainly attributed to: 
• Funding received for the Disaster Financial Assistance Arrangements from Budget 2019 ($155 million);  
Offset by:  
• A transfer to the Royal Canadian Mounted Police for the First Nations Community Policing Service ($52.9 million). 

The increase of 69 FTEs from the 2019-20 Planned FTEs to the 2019-20 Actual FTEs is mainly due to hiring in support of the Passenger Protect Program, Investment Canada Act, the Government Operations Centre Modernization Project, and the Government Operations Centre as well as the implementation of new initiatives in 2019-20, such as the National Cyber Security Strategy and the Emergency Management Strategy.

footnote_fr:
Les dépenses  réelles en 2019-2020 sont en hausse de 191,7 millions de dollars (26 %) par rapport aux dépenses en 2018-2019. Cette augmentation est essentiellement attribuable aux facteurs suivants :  
• une augmentation du niveau de financement pour le programme des Accords d’aide financière en cas de catastrophe (90,1 millions de dollars);  
• une subvention législative unique au Shock Trauma Air Rescue Service (65 millions de dollars);  
